                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Imagine, if you will, a potentially dangerous ritual, that might attract the attention of undesirables... namely void demons. Whilst I'm aware of the protocols for transporting from a transport circle, things get a little more complicated when ritual circles are involved.
<br />

<br />
Does the seal need to be in a particular state? If so, which?
<br />
Can the transport occur during a ritual? Is this likely to be unsafe?
<br />
Is an accidently summoned void demon likely to follow you, or munch on the unsuspecting victims... uh, I mean audience...?
<br />
Are there any side-effects? Would it make a ritual less effective, compared to finishing the ritual, dropping the seal and running away?
<br />

<br />
It just seems so... useful... that fourteen others can be transported, and that fourteen others can be used to help control and shape the ritual.
<br />

<br />
(As an aside, what counts as an 'other'? Do unliving count? Do void demons count? Admittedly, neither is likely to be contributing to a ritual.)
<br />

<br />
Ruthien mel Tresic,
<br />
Viper ambassador to the Lions.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
