                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As far as I understand things, when you transport via a transport circle, you actually travel through the barrier that surrounds Erdreja, through the planes of light I'm told.
<br />
When you seal a circle, the seal which is the barrier drops and forms the seal around the circle, thereby giving you direct access to void energies.  You <span style="font-style: italic">can</span> then transport people to another ritual circle by travelling through the void rather than through the planes of light.  To me, this sounds rather dangerous, but it does have the added benefit that you're able to travel outside of Erdreja this way.
<br />
I'm only about 90% sure of what I've said here.  If anyone can correct me on the bits that aren't quite true I'd be grateful!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
